5:
Hm, the village that put in the
request to the Diviners' Commission
should be around here.
8:
Malicious yokai are said to have
taken up residence nearby. We'd
best approach with caution.
11:
I've found you, yokai! Get away from
him!
15:
Cripes, you dodged my attack! I was
sure I had you!
21:
Good lord! What do you think you're
doing!
25:
I refuse to tell my name to the likes
of yokai who would assail the village!
26:
As long as I, Kuramaru, stand, you
won't be hurting anyone! Unhand
that man at once!
30:
So much for not telling us your
name...
36:
This isn't the first time I've had
suspicion cast on me. Though I am
no yokai; I am human.
39:
And I'm not exactly being held
captive either.
44:
Hm, I suppose you're not up to any
mischief...
47: But you sure don't look human..
52:
Looks like you decide if someone's
good or bad depending on if they're
a yokai?
55:
That's right! It's always the yokai that
go around hurting people after all!
60:
Hrm... Anyhow, I'll say it again, but I
am not a yokai.
64:
I can vouch for him. He's simply
taking the form of an animal right
now.
69:
Oh, I know! A yokai must've
transformed you!
71:
Tell me where that yokai is! I'll take
care of the problem for you!
75:
Well, I'm not sure I'd call the Lord of
Shadow a yokai—
79: Aha, he must be human then.
82:
He's... not exactly human either. He's
appeared countless times
throughout history as an enemy of
mankind.
87:
A-anyway! It's a funny coincidence
that we've also come to hunt down
yokai!
91:
Ah, you two must be the help that
village elder mentioned!
92: C'mon, I'll bring you guys to him!
99:
Blasted yokai! I won't let any harm
come to the village!
105:
Rgh... How awful! Don't think you're
getting away with this, yokai!
113:
Not much of a conversationalist, is
he?
116:
They've gone too far. We may need
a show of force.
119: That's what I like to hear! Let's go!
136:
Good thing you're not hurt too bad.
I'll go get the doctor!
144:
Light, doesn't it seem odd to you for
yokai to steal rice?
148:
Good point. As far as I know, rice
doesn't have any special value to
them.
153:
The doctor'll be here in a jiffy! So
what were you two talking about?
158: Oh, it's nothing! Don't worry about it!
161:
What now? Should we report to the
village elder?
164:
Yeah, we probably should. Which
reminds me—
168:
On our way to see the elder, I wanna
hear more about that yokai you call
the Lord of Shadow!
172:
I said he's not a yokai... Well, never
mind that.
174:
It all began before I came to this
world—
178:
So you've protected people from all
sorts of yokai, huh?
184:
All right, I've decided! I'm coming
along with you two.
187:
After all, I made a promise to my
father that I'd help out people in
need!
191:
While we appreciate the sentiment,
among us are—
196:
Sounds good to me! We welcome
you with open arms, Kuramaru!
200:
Wouldn't that put our yokai friends in
danger?
203:
Which is exactly why I'd like him to
see with his own eyes that not all
yokai are bad. That'd be better for
all of us.
204:
And having him travel with us would
let him see that firsthand.
209:
You're right; he's a bit of a wild card.
Leaving him be would only cause
bigger problems.
214:
Hey, what are you guys whispering
about?
220:
Oh, don't mind us! We were just
talking about what to do afterward!
224:
The journey ahead will be much
easier with you among our group.
It's a pleasure to have you,
Kuramaru.
227:
Ehehe, glad to hear it! Leave all the
yokai to me!
